verses.text: Now Benjamin begat Bela his firstborn , Ashbel the second , and Aharah the third ,
Nohah the fourth , and Rapha the fifth.
And the sons of Bela were, Addar , and Gera , and Abihud ,\f + \fr 8.3 \ft Addar: or, Ard\f*
And Abishua , and Naaman , and Ahoah ,
And Gera , and Shephuphan , and Huram.\f + \fr 8.5 \ft Shephuphan: or, Shupham\f*
And these \add are\add* the sons of Ehud : these are the heads of the fathers of the inhabitants of Geba , and they removed them to Manahath :
And Naaman , and Ahiah , and Gera , he removed them, and begat Uzza , and Ahihud.
And Shaharaim begat \add children\add* in the country of Moab , after he had sent them away ; Hushim and Baara \add were\add* his wives.
And he begat of Hodesh his wife , Jobab , and Zibia , and Mesha , and Malcham ,
And Jeuz , and Shachia , and Mirma. These \add were\add* his sons , heads of the fathers.
And of Hushim he begat Abitub , and Elpaal.
The sons of Elpaal ; Eber , and Misham , and Shamed , who built Ono , and Lod , with the towns thereof:
Beriah also, and Shema , who \add were\add* heads of the fathers of the inhabitants of Aijalon , who drove away the inhabitants of Gath :
And Ahio , Shashak , and Jeremoth ,
And Zebadiah , and Arad , and Ader ,
And Michael , and Ispah , and Joha , the sons of Beriah ;
And Zebadiah , and Meshullam , and Hezeki , and Heber ,
Ishmerai also, and Jezliah , and Jobab , the sons of Elpaal ;
And Jakim , and Zichri , and Zabdi ,
And Elienai , and Zilthai , and Eliel ,
And Adaiah , and Beraiah , and Shimrath , the sons of Shimhi ;\f + \fr 8.21 \ft Shimhi: or, Shema\f*
And Ishpan , and Heber , and Eliel ,
And Abdon , and Zichri , and Hanan ,
And Hananiah , and Elam , and Antothijah ,
And Iphedeiah , and Penuel , the sons of Shashak ;
And Shamsherai , and Shehariah , and Athaliah ,
And Jaresiah , and Eliah , and Zichri , the sons of Jeroham.
These \add were\add* heads of the fathers , by their generations , chief \add men\add*. These dwelt in Jerusalem.
And at Gibeon dwelt the father of Gibeon ; whose wife’s name \add was\add* Maachah :\f + \fr 8.29 \ft father…: also called Jehiel\f*
And his firstborn son Abdon , and Zur , and Kish , and Baal , and Nadab ,
And Gedor , and Ahio , and Zacher.\f + \fr 8.31 \ft Zacher: or, Zechariah\f*
And Mikloth begat Shimeah. And these also dwelt with their brethren in Jerusalem , over against them.\f + \fr 8.32 \ft Shimeah: or, Shimeam\f* \p

¶ And Ner begat Kish , and Kish begat Saul , and Saul begat Jonathan , and Malchi-shua , and Abinadab , and Esh-baal.\f + \fr 8.33 \ft Abinadab: also called, Ishui\f*\f + \fr 8.33 \ft Esh-baal: or, Ish-bosheth\f*
And the son of Jonathan \add was\add* Merib-baal ; and Merib-baal begat Micah.\f + \fr 8.34 \ft Merib-baal: or, Mephibosheth\f*
And the sons of Micah \add were\add*, Pithon , and Melech , and Tarea , and Ahaz.\f + \fr 8.35 \ft Tarea: or, Tahrea\f*
And Ahaz begat Jehoadah ; and Jehoadah begat Alemeth , and Azmaveth , and Zimri ; and Zimri begat Moza ,\f + \fr 8.36 \ft Jehoadah: also called, Jarah\f*
And Moza begat Binea : Rapha \add was\add* his son , Eleasah his son , Azel his son :\f + \fr 8.37 \ft Rapha: also called, Rephaiah\f*
And Azel had six sons , whose names \add are\add* these, Azrikam , Bocheru , and Ishmael , and Sheariah , and Obadiah , and Hanan. All these \add were\add* the sons of Azel.
And the sons of Eshek his brother \add were\add*, Ulam his firstborn , Jehush the second , and Eliphelet the third.
And the sons of Ulam were mighty men of valour , archers , and had many sons , and sons’ sons , an hundred and fifty. All these \add are\add* of the sons of Benjamin.
